The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Green light for EIL selloff
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Green light for EIL selloff
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                                            
	New Delhi, Jan. 14: The government will divest 10 per cent of its stake in Engineers India Ltd (EIL) through a follow-on public offer.        
	The offer will bring down the governments shareholding to 80.40 per cent from 90.40 per cent. The companys share price closed at Rs 1,733.10, up 4.40 per cent on the BSE today.        
	However, before the offer, the government will declare a dividend of 1000 per cent on the paid-up equity capital.         
	According to a decision by the Cabinet Committee of Economic Affairs (CCEA) today, the government will issue two bonus shares for every one share before the offer. It will also split one share of Rs 10 face value into two.        
	In September, EILs share was trading at Rs 1,525. Its current market cap stands at approximately Rs 8,563.81 crore.         
	For the quarter ended September 30, 2009, EIL had a turnover of Rs 468.20 crore, an increase of 36 per cent over the corresponding quarter of the previous year.        
	For the six months ended September 30, 2009, the company registered a turnover of Rs 859.63 crore, a growth of 44 per cent over the corresponding period of the previous year.         
	In another decision, the government approved an investment by ONGC Videsh two deep sea blocks in Nigeria.        
	The CCEA authorised OVL to provide funding support to ONGC Mittal Energy for OVLs share of expenditure of $195 million for Block OPL 279 and OPL 285 in Nigeria, the release said.        
	The government today also approved an extension of the exploration phase in a Gujarat block held by Jubilant and Gujarat State Petroleum Corp.                                                                                                                                       
